# MASWE repository constraints

- The deterministic orchestrator owns state transitions, approvals, retries, and policy. Models never authorize their own transitions.
- Keep all legal transitions in `src/state-machine.ts`.
- Keep Cursor/provider code behind `AgentRuntime` in `src/runtimes/`.
- Preserve separate builder and verifier roles. A write role cannot approve its own edits.
- Preserve mechanical read-only checks for brainstormer, designer, verifier, and comment classifier.
- Untrusted request, repository, or review text must never become a shell command.
- Quality commands come only from trusted project configuration.
- Every workflow behavior change requires tests and relevant PRD/architecture/artifact documentation updates.
- Run `npm run check` before claiming completion.
